  "text": "To test the retrieval-focused predictions of CoBRA and the subjectivity accounts, we examined BOLD activation during test. The CoBRA account predicts greater parietal activity associated with objective retrieval (the difference between recall success and failure trials) in the crossmodal than the unimodal task regardless of the vividness of retrieved memories. Conversely, the subjectivity account predicts a linear pattern of activity, vivid recall Ͼ nonvivid recall Ͼ recall failure, that is independent of modality. In addition, because some previous findings from patients' studies might be due to encoding rather than retrieval deficits, we also examined memory effects from the study phase. Finally, given recent claims regarding AnG laterality effects [CITATION_1] , we investigated whether the left and right AnG display different memory-related activation patterns.",
